              "type": "text",
              "text": "List comprehensions provide a concise way to create lists. The syntax is: [expression for item in iterable if condition]\n\nExamples:\n- Squares: [x**2 for x in range(10)]\n- Even numbers: [x for x in range(20) if x % 2 == 0]\n- Uppercase: [word.upper() for word in ['hello', 'world']]\n\nThey are generally faster than equivalent for-loops for simple transformations."
